reek, based on Demotic, is the\nofficial language of both Greece and Cyprus. Greek is spoken today by\napproximately 12-15 million people, mainly in Greece and Cyprus, but also by\nminority and immigrant communities in many other countries.\n","linknr":716,"url":"Modern_Greek","recorded":1362540697,"links":78,"instances":["linguistics","aeolis","diacritic","orthography","phonetics","linguistics","country","orthography","greece","process","grammatical_number","phonetics"],"pdf":["http://www.benjamins.com/jbp/series/JGL/4/art/0003a.pdf","http://www.ilsp.gr/files/Glossary-Filoglossia.pdf","http://www.ilsp.gr/files/Basic_Greek_Grammar.pdf"],"categories":["Modern Greek language|"],"headings":["Classification","Geographic distribution","Official status","Varieties","Demotic as Koiné (Standard) Modern Greek","Phonology","Grammar","Examples","Sample text","Notes","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b7/Flag_of_Europe.svg/22px-Flag_of_Europe.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5c/Flag_of_Greece.svg/22px-Flag_of_Greece.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d4/Flag_of_Cyprus.svg/22px-Flag_of_Cyprus.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/36/Flag_of_Albania.svg/22px-Flag_of_Albania.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2f/Flag_of_Armenia.svg/22px-Flag_of_Armenia.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/0/03/Flag_of_Italy.svg/22px-Flag_of_Italy.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/73/Flag_of_Romania.svg/22px-Flag_of_Romania.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Flag_of_Turkey.svg/22px-Flag_of_Turkey.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/49/Flag_of_Ukraine.svg/22px-Flag_of_Ukraine.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5c/P46.jpg/180px-P46.jpg","//u